-- Korea Aerospace wins $1 billion order for fighter jets
-- 
-- Mon May 6, 2013 8:44pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/05/07/us-kai-order-idUSBRE94600C20130507

 

 SEOUL  (Reuters) - Korea Aerospace Industries Ltd (KAI) ( 047810.KS ) has won a 1.12 trillion won ($1.02 billion) order to supply an unnamed number of FA-50 fighter jets to South Korea's military through the Defense Acquisition Program Administration (DAPA). 
 The South Korean aircraft maker said in a regulatory filing on Tuesday that the contract is based on an initial mass-production agreement reached in December 2011, and will last until October of 2016. ($1 = 1094.4500 Korean won) (Reporting by Joyce Lee; Editing by  Daniel Magnowski )